news.title: Bhubaneswar development body reviews progress of town planning schemes
news.para: BDA has made significant progress, completing 60 km of embankment road and 64.9 km of drainage work. The authority also constructed 29 culverts and finished 4 km of bitumen work in designated areas.

news.title: Of six illegal colonies identified, one razed in last three months in Panchkula
news.para: In a recent meeting of the district-level task force formed to tackle illegal encroachments and unauthorised colonies, deputy commissioner Monica Gupta issued a clear mandate to departments concerned to eliminate illegal construction in the district.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: 100 construction workers get housing allocation orders
news.para: Organized by the Tamil Nadu Construction Workers' Welfare Board, commercial taxes minister P Moorthy, IT minister Palanivel Thiaga Rajan and labour welfare minister C V Ganesan took part in it.

news.title: Raipur civic body's 1,500 crore budget prioritises urban development
news.para: The city will receive three working women's hostels and restrooms, complete with sanitary vending machines and baby feeding facilities. The plans include a children's play area and youth library.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body to install 4,500 LED streetlights across Salt Lake & Rajarhat-Gopalpur
news.para: As per the plan, 405 LEDs of 90-watt, costing about Rs 1.6 crore, and 4,060 of 45 and 60-watt capacities, priced at Rs 2 crore, will be installed on new steel poles.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 1,205 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: On Saturday, 1,205 commercial properties were sealed in the West Zone of the city, while notices were issued to 2,746 residential properties. In just one day, property tax revenue of Rs 2.48 crore was collected in the West Zone.

news.title: ED attaches shops in TDI Mall over environment pollution-linked PMLA case
news.para: Eight commercial spaces or shops in TDI Mall at GT Road, Kundli (Sonipat), have been provisionally attached under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA), the Enforcement Directorate (ED) said in a statement.

news.title: DLF’s chairman warns of ‘flattening of the sales curve’
news.para: Singh said the company is trying it’s best to stay away from speculators, who overtrades, take advantage of the installment payment schemes and try to make bookings which at the end of the day cannot be funded unless somebody else is found to take them off his hand.

news.title: MCD collaborates with HUDCO for redevelopment of key properties in Delhi
news.para: A committee, set up two months ago with members from both agencies, is examining the key aspects, and both organisations are likely to soon finalise a memorandum of understanding regarding development guidelines, said MCD officials.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Farmers to get four times the circle rate for Harnandipuram land
news.para: The decision was taken by a six-member committee headed by district magistrate Deepak Meena, in keeping with the Land Acquisition (Rehabilitation & Resettlement) Act, 2013.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 44 crore assets of builder Lalit Tekchandani, including Dubai villa
news.para: The attached properties include a villa in Dubai, residential and commercial properties in Mumbai, land parcels in Pune, and fixed deposits. Previously, ED had frozen and seized investment worth Rs 158 crore in the same case.

news.title: Noida homebuyers oppose proposal to hike circle rates
news.para: In a letter to the DM, Noida Extension Flat Owners and Members Association (NEFOMA), a registered umbrella body of 80 housing complexes, highlighted multiple concerns, including unresolved property registrations and inadequate civic amenities.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body seals 25 shops of tax & rent defaulters
news.para: The civic body's estate officer Vilas Salokhe said, "Several shopkeepers owed rent to the KMC for their shops owned by the civic body in several commercial markets of the city since 2015."

news.title: Greater Noida authority increases land rates by 5% across all categories
news.para: In residential areas, including Alpha 1, 2, Gamma 1, 2, Beta 1, 2, Delta 1, 2, 3, Swarn Nagri and sectors 1, 2, 3, 4, 10, 12, 16 and 16C, land rate was revised from Rs 47,227 per square metre to Rs 49,588 per sqm.

news.title: Delhi civic body attaches 88 properties, 87 bank accounts of tax defaulters
news.para: In City SP zone, 22 properties and 19 bank accounts were attached, resulting in a recovery of Rs 65.24 lakh. Similarly, in Civil Lines zone, 45 properties and nine bank accounts were attached, recovering Rs 187.46 lakh.

news.title: Nagpur Smart City projects to be handed over to NMC by March 31
news.para: As there is no confirmation about an extension from the ministry of housing and urban affairs (MoHUA), the tenure of the special purpose vehicle (SPV) is set to end on March 31, 2025.

news.title: Cineline India sells hotel property in Goa for Rs 270 crore
news.para: Cineline India is planning to utilize the sale proceeds to fully repay its outstanding debt of Rz 108 crores related to the film exhibition business, achieving a debt-free status.

news.title: Civic bodies in Delhi extend property tax office hours to boost collections
news.para: NDMC set a target of collecting Rs 1,150 crore through service tax for the financial year 2024-2025 and has already surpassed Rs 1,000 crore.

news.title: EPC model for Visakhapatnam, Vijayawada metro projects
news.para: If interim consultants were appointed instead, they would charge approximately 0.2% of the project cost — around Rs 20 crore — for a 12-month period, to assist with preliminary activities till general consultants are engaged.

news.title: Nashik civic body issues warrants to 426 property tax defaulters
news.para: NMC took the step after serving two notices over the last three months, asking 5000 defaulters to clear payments before March end. Officials said they want to recover as much property tax dues as possible by March 31.
